  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Cleopatra VII
Lived:         69 - -30
Nationality:   Egyptian
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Last pharaoh of Egypt
Contribution:  Spoke 9 languages; allied with Caesar and Mark Antony; end of pharaonic era
Quote:         "I will not be triumphed over."

Name:          Charles Darwin
Lived:         1809 - 1882
Nationality:   English
Field:         Biology
Known For:     Evolution by Natural Selection
Contribution:  On the Origin of Species; explained diversity of life on Earth
Quote:         "It is not the strongest that survives, but the most adaptable."

Name:          Galileo Galilei
Lived:         1564 - 1642
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Astronomy
Known For:     Heliocentrism, telescope
Contribution:  Confirmed Copernican model; law of falling bodies; faced Inquisition
Quote:         "And yet it moves."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

